That’s because the binary still expects the optimized version. The workspace feature is only for lib; the binary inherits from it unless you set a separate block like `features = ["opt"]`. Here's an example:
```
workspace {
  name = "myproj"
}
lib {
  path = "./lib.rs"
  features = ["opt", "not-optimized"]
}
binary {
  path = "main.rs"
  features = ["opt"] // only opt, not not-optimized
}
```

